  "graph": {
    "note": "Conformance fixtures for the intent-graph read model (ADR-0014, schema/intent-graph.schema.json). Unlike the catalog vectors these pin STRUCTURE, not ETags: the graph is not a synced wire artifact in v1. Both producers — the in-process local learner and the Ratel Cloud builder — MUST emit graphs that validate, and every consumer MUST reject the `invalid` set.",
    "consumerRules": [
      "An edge naming a capability absent from the consumer's registry MUST be dropped, never ranked — the catalog may have changed since the graph was grown.",
      "`centroid` MAY be absent; a consumer without an embedder matches lexically over `members`, and one with an embedder MAY derive a centroid from `members`.",
      "A consumer MUST NOT mix centroids produced by different embedding models; on a model change, discard the centroids and re-derive from `members`.",
      "`label` and `terms` are display-only. Retrieval results MUST be identical whatever they contain.",
      "Only the relative order of edge weights within a cluster is load-bearing; absolute magnitudes are never compared against BM25 or cosine scores."
    ],
